  "body": "<!--NOTE:\r\n- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\n\r\nHaving typed errors is very useful to programatically interact with them. However their e.message is very uninformative on its own. We rely on our logger to print the error metadata nicely. If the error is shown outside of Lodestar run time, the e.message will be displayed alone. Also, turning the error metadata into a string automatically is more expensive than doing it manually.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n\r\nAdd a function that turns error types into message strings.\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nexport enum EpochContextErrorCode {\r\n  COMMITTEE_INDEX_OUT_OF_RANGE = \"EPOCH_CONTEXT_ERROR_COMMITTEE_INDEX_OUT_OF_RANGE\",\r\n}\r\n\r\ntype EpochContextErrorType = {\r\n  code: EpochContextErrorCode.COMMITTEE_INDEX_OUT_OF_RANGE;\r\n  index: number;\r\n  maxIndex: number;\r\n};\r\n\r\nexport class EpochContextError extends LodestarError<EpochContextErrorType> {\r\n  constructor(type: EpochContextErrorType) {\r\n    super(type, getEpochContextErrorMessage(type));\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction getEpochContextErrorMessage(type: EpochContextErrorType): string {\r\n  switch (type.code) {\r\n    case EpochContextErrorCode.COMMITTEE_INDEX_OUT_OF_RANGE:\r\n      return `${type.code} index=${type.index} maxIndex=${type.maxIndex}`;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen we can decide what error data is relevant to be printed and do the minimal work necessary.",
